New Records: David Miller scored the most runs at the Nassau County Ground with 59 off 51 balls
Key Match Events: Quinton de Kock was run out without facing in the first over
Reeza Hendricks was clean-bowled by Logan van Beek in the second over
Aiden Markram was caught down the leg side by Viv Kingma
Heinrich Klaasen was caught at deep square leg by Viv Kingma
David Miller and Tristan Stubbs shared a stand of 65
Sybrand Engelbrecht and Logan van Beek cobbled together 54 for the seventh wicket
David Miller hit three sixes and a four to win the match for South Africa
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Netherlands won this fixture in the last T20 World Cup and the ODI version last year
The result must count as yet another upset in a week that’s been full of them
New York has hosted four World Cup games in the last week, and the locals are starting to feel familiar with cricket
Others: Marco Jansen’s height made him almost unplayable on this springy pitch
Anrich Nortje’s pace was hardly any easier to face
Sybrand Engelbrecht was born and raised in South Africa and played alongside Hendricks in the national U19 team at the World Cup back in 2008
